        "a": "a. Definition of the Trinity\n1. \"God eternally exists as three persons, Father, Son, and Holy Spirit, and each person is fully God, and there is one God.\"\nb. Biblical Defense of the Trinity\n1. God exists as three persons\n- Matthew 3:16-17: During Jesus' baptism, the Spirit descended upon him, and the Father spoke from heaven saying that he was well-pleased with Jesus his son. Thus God exists as three distinct persons.\n- Matthew 28:18-20\n2. Each person is fully God — God the Father is God — Deuteronomy 6:4: \"Hear, O Israel: The LORD our God, the LORD is one.\"\n3. God the Son is God — John 1:1: \"In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.\"\n4. God the Holy Spirit is God — Acts 5:3-4: \"Then Peter said, 'Ananias, how is it that Satan has so filled your heart that you have lied to the Holy Spirit...You have not lied to men but to God.'\"\nc. There is one God\n1. 1 Timothy 2:5: \"For there is one God and one mediator between God and men, the man Christ Jesus....\"",
