        "q": "Distinguish the Reformed and Arminian understandings of these doctrines.",
        "a": "a. Arminians do not accept the Reformed doctrine of absolute predestination. Rather, they support the doctrine of conditional predestination, that is, that God predestined His \"elect\" based conditionally upon His foreknowledge that they would believe. They incorrectly interpret foreknowledge as pertaining only to one's choice of Christ rather than to one's person, often citing 1 Peter 1:2, which says that the elect were chosen according to foreknowledge. Such a view, however, puts salvation ultimately into the hands of man.",
