        "q": "What is saving faith? Defend your answer with Scripture proofs.",
        "a": "a. Saving faith is faith in Jesus Christ.\nb. WSC 86: \"Faith in Jesus Christ is a saving grace, whereby we receive and rest upon him alone for salvation, as he is offered to us in the gospel.\"\n1. John 1:12: \"Yet to all who received him, to those who believed in his name, he gave the right to become children of God....\"\n2. Romans 10:9: \"That if you confess with your mouth, 'Jesus is Lord,' and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.\"",
